	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />$4301 isn't just the <em>starting</em> location, <em>every</em> byte in the DMA block get sent to that address, so DMA only does anything useful to registers $2104, $2118 and $2122.  All three have there own corrisponding address register, so why don't they just combine all three and cut out the middle man?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


